Art. 4.71. 
Principle of net partition 
Any co-heir who is liable for the payment of the debts and expenses of the succession may require that such debts and expenses be paid before proceeding with the partition in kind, and that, if necessary, undivided property be sold beforehand, if the bank accounts and portfolio securities belonging to the general body of creditors do not appear to be sufficient.   ¤ 
2. undivided assets are allocated to the discharge of liabilities in the following order: 
1¡ cash and bank accounts; 
2¡ public funds, registered securities, debts and other intangible movable property; 
3¡ tangible movable property; 
4¡ immovable property.
Any co-heir may nevertheless prevent the sale referred to in paragraph 1 by providing sufficient security against any recourse.
If the co-heirs do not agree as to which property is to be sold by priority, the question is submitted to and decided within the framework of the judicial partition.
